[SN]TITLE[SN]
Burpham attack: Three men charged with affray

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Three men have been charged with affray after a man was hit by a van during a suspected murder attempt in Surrey.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The 21-year-old suffered serious head, arm and leg injuries in Bowers Farm Drive, Burpham, Guildford, on 12 May.
Iain Vase, 29, of Pond Meadow, Shaun Ritson, 31, of Lime Grove and Darren Harms, 47, of Lime Grove - all in Guildford, are due in court on 21 June.
Last month, Raymond Harms faced two counts of attempted murder, dangerous driving, affray and criminal damage.
The charges also related to incidents that occurred in Lawrence Close on the same evening.
Mr Harms, 25, from Guildford, is due to stand trial at Guildford Crown Court on 10 October.
